Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.05,0:06:28.25,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}中文书写形式的规范\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the Chinese language was to be written,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.05,0:06:28.25,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}书同文
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.29,0:06:33.32,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}也包括了什么是可以写 什么是可以想的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}including what you were allowed to write and think.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.29,0:06:33.32,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}秦始皇以严刑峻罚来控制臣民思想\n使臣民不敢反抗 从而达到顺利推行政
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.36,0:06:36.13,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}秦始皇的哲学 唯一他认可的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Emperor Qin's philosophy-- the only one permitted--
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.16,0:06:37.76,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}即法家
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.16,0:06:37.76,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}称之 守法主义\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}was called "legalism,"
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.80,0:06:40.36,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就如同它的字面意思\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which is just what it sounded like,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.40,0:06:43.80,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}遵纪守法 否则就...\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}do as the law says... or else.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.24,0:06:46.87,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这种哲学理论对于质疑权威\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's a philosophy that's not highly conducive
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.90,0:06:49.91,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}不是十分有利\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to questioning authority.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.98,0:06:56.78,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}百家思想的书籍\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}...that all the books of the hundred schools of thought
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.81,0:06:58.45,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}统统烧掉\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}shall be be burned,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.48,0:07:01.89,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}以古讽今者\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that anyone who uses history to criticize the present
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.92,0:07:04.19,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}全家处斩\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}shall have his family executed.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.22,0:07:08.33,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}墨子和孔子的著作\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The works of MoTze and Confucius
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.36,0:07:10.56,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}还有其它哲人的作品\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and other philosophers were destroyed
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.60,0:07:12.56,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}尽毁于世界历史上首次的焚书\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the world's first book burning.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.60,0:07:15.17,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}数百名书生英勇抵抗\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Hundreds of scholars bravely resisted
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.20,0:07:17.90,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}试图保护这些禁书\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}by trying to preserve the forbidden books.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.94,0:07:20.54,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在首都将他们活埋\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They were buried alive in the capitol.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.94,0:07:20.54,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}咸阳的"焚书坑儒"
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.27,0:07:26.08,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}科学需要有自由的表达才能繁荣发展\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Science needs the light of free expression to flourish.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.11,0:07:29.48,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}需要无畏的质疑权威\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It depends on the fearless questioning of authority,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.51,0:07:32.08,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}开放的交流思想\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the open exchange of ideas.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.12,0:07:35.82,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}墨子和他的追随者们所记载的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Sparks of curiosity in the writings of Mo Tze
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.85,0:07:39.59,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}突发奇想都被抹杀了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and his disciples were effectively stomped out.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.62,0:07:44.23,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}影片的再次出现 已是另一个千年之后\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It would be another thousand years before the next movie.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.13,0:07:48.37,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}幸运的是 我们的想象之舟\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Luckily, our Ship of the Imagination
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.40,0:07:52.40,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}可以带我们去任何的空间和时间\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}can take us anywhere in space... and time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.64,0:08:05.31,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}中国和希腊的古人发现\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The ancient Chinese and Greeks observed
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.34,0:08:06.98,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}光线可以展现出各种神奇\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that light could be made
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.01,0:08:09.81,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但是却没人去问\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to do wonderful things-- but no one asked that question
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.85,0:08:15.12,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}小孩子和天才们喜欢问的问题  为什么\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}favored by small children and geniuses alike. Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.15,0:08:18.19,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}直到一千年前\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Until a thousand years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.29,0:08:25.63,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}伊拉克的巴斯拉城\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In the city of Basra, Iraq,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.66,0:08:27.63,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}生活着另一位光线大师\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}there lived another master of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.66,0:08:33.00,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}海桑极度渴望了解自然\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Ibn al-Hazen had a passionate desire to understand nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.04,0:08:35.14,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他对一切都有疑问\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He questioned everything,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.17,0:08:39.11,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}特别是那些别人认为理所应当的事情\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}especially those things that everyone else took for granted.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.04,0:08:44.25,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们怎么能看到  他问\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}"How do we see?" he asked.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.28,0:08:46.65,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}有些在他之前的伟大权威\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Some of the great authorities who came before him
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.68,0:08:50.25,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}认为光线从我们的眼中出发\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}had taught that rays come out of our eyes and travel
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.29,0:08:54.62,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在物体上反射 然后返回我们的眼中\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to the objects we see before returning to our eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.66,0:08:58.53,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但海桑不认同 理由是恒星离我们那么远\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But al-Hazen reasoned that the stars were too far distant
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.56,0:09:01.13,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}什么东西可以从我们眼中射向星星\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for something in our eyes to travel all the way to them
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.16,0:09:03.80,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}并在一眨眼的时间内返回\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and back in the blink of an eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.83,0:09:07.47,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}很有道理  但海桑并未止步\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Excellent reasoning, but al-Hazen didn't stop there.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.50,0:09:11.77,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他绞尽脑汁探索大自然的奥秘\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He searched for ways to compel nature to divulge her secrets.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.81,0:09:15.11,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当时他的文化对于新的见解与质疑是开放的态度\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}His culture was open to new ideas and questioning.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.15,0:09:17.61,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那是科学发展的黄金时代\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It was the golden age of science
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.65,0:09:19.85,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在伊斯兰世界\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the Islamic world.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.88,0:09:23.32,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}伊斯兰世界从西班牙的科索瓦\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One that stretched from Cordoba in Spain
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.35,0:09:26.96,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一直延伸到中亚的撒马尔罕\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}all the way to Samarkand in Central Asia.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.99,0:09:29.99,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}基督教和犹太教的学者被敬为上宾\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Christian and Jewish scholars were honored guests
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.03,0:09:32.73,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在开罗  巴格达的研究机构\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}at the research institutes of Baghdad, Cairo,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.76,0:09:35.30,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}和其它伊斯兰世界的中心\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and other Islamic capitols.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.33,0:09:38.87,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}不同于秦始皇  哈里发们派遣使者\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Instead of burning books, the caliphs sent emissaries
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.33,0:09:38.87,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}哈里发是穆斯林统治者的称号
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.90,0:09:41.84,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在世界各地搜集书籍\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}around the world in search of books.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.62,0:10:00.02,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}哈里发们大量的资助将这些书籍\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The caliphs lavishly funded projects to translate, study,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.06,0:10:02.26,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}翻译 研究  并保存  流传后世\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and preserve them for future generations.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.29,0:10:05.23,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}多亏了他们的努力  许多古希腊科学家的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Much of the light of Ancient Greek science would have been
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.26,0:10:07.70,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}成果才得以保存\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}permanently extinguished without their efforts.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.73,0:10:10.53,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}对科学的狂热在欧洲再次兴起\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The reawakening to science that took place in Europe,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.57,0:10:13.60,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}发生在几百年后 多亏了伊斯兰学者和\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}hundreds of years later, was kindled by a flame
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.64,0:10:14.87,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}科学家对这些文献的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that had been long tended
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.91,0:10:17.77,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}精心呵护\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}by Islamic scholars and scientists.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.81,0:10:21.34,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}阿拉伯人将新思想由印度传入西方\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Arabs also imported ideas from India to the West,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.38,0:10:23.95,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}包括所谓的  阿拉伯数字\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}including the so-called Arabic numerals
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.98,0:10:26.25,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们至今都在使用\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that we all use today,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.28,0:10:29.08,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}还有数字0\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the concept of zero...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.76,0:10:33.22,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}确实很方便\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which comes in handy
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.26,0:10:36.69,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}特别是当你书写 几十亿又几十亿时\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when you want to write "billions and billions."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.73,0:10:39.70,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}阿拉伯天文学十分具有影响力\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Arabic astronomy was so influential,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.73,0:10:41.76,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们至今依然用阿拉伯语名字来称呼\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that we still call most of the bright stars
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.80,0:10:43.60,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那些明亮的恒星\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}by their Arabic names.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.63,0:10:48.70,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}代数  算法  炼金术  酒精 这些英语单词中的 al\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And the "al's" in algebra, algorithm, alchemy, and alcohol
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.74,0:10:50.44,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}证明了阿拉伯语\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are just some of the traces left
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.47,0:10:54.94,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}是科学界的通用语言\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from the time when Arabic was the language of science.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.85,0:10:59.58,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}11世纪时  海桑准备尝试\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In the 11th century, Ibn al-Hazen set about trying
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.62,0:11:03.65,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}验证他关于光和我们如何看见的理论\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to test his ideas about light and how we see.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.69,0:11:06.92,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们设计了一套实验测定光线如何移动\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So we devised an experiment to determine how light moves.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.96,0:11:09.33,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们在烈日下支起一顶帐篷\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We erected a tent in full daylight
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.36,0:11:12.46,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}将它完全密封 只允许一束光穿过\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and sealed it tightly so that only a single ray of light
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.50,0:11:15.23,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}射入内部的黑暗中\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}could pierce its inner darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.27,0:11:17.57,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他用他的智慧\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}With little more than his brains
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.60,0:11:19.84,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}加上一件笔直的木质工具  尺子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and a straight piece of wood-- a ruler--
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.87,0:11:21.74,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}海桑完成了一次科学历史上\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}al-Hazen had accomplished a great leap forward
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.77,0:11:23.31,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}伟大的跨越\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the history of science.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.34,0:11:27.34,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他发现光线呈直线运动\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He discovered that light moves in straight lines.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.52,0:11:34.48,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这只是开始\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But he was just getting started.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.52,0:11:37.92,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}海桑总结出成像的关键\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Al-Hazen figured out that the key to forming any image--
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.95,0:11:40.99,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}不论 眼睛还是照相机暗箱\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}whether you're talking about an eye or camera obscura--
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.02,0:11:43.69,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}都是通过控制光线进入\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is a small opening to restrict the light that can enter
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.73,0:11:45.59,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}黑暗内室的小孔\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}an otherwise darkened chamber.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.63,0:11:48.50,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}光圈将我们周遭繁杂无关的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That aperture excludes the chaos
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.53,0:11:51.20,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}光线排除在外\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of extraneous light rays that surround us.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.23,0:11:52.87,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}光圈越小\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The smaller the aperture,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.90,0:11:55.44,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}进入的光线角度范围越小\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the fewer directions that light can come from.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.47,0:11:57.64,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}使图像更清晰\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And that makes the image sharper.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.67,0:12:00.44,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}从而不至于让光线致盲\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So instead of being blinded by the light,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.48,0:12:03.65,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们可以分辨光线呈现的图像\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we can see everything it has to show us.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.68,0:12:06.98,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}海桑亲自做出了他的暗箱\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Al-Hazen made his own camera obscura
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.02,0:12:09.05,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}令哈里发们赞叹不已\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and dazzled the caliphs.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.09,0:12:12.15,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}有效的暗箱需要明亮的光线\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A camera obscura works best in bright light.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.19,0:12:15.99,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}夜空中的星光对它来说太暗淡了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The stars of the night sky are way too dim for this.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.03,0:12:19.33,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们需要更大的孔来收集光线\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We somehow need a bigger opening to collect light,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.36,0:12:21.80,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}同时我们需要保持焦点\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but we also need to maintain focus.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.83,0:12:24.47,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}望远镜从视野的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A telescope collects light
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.50,0:12:26.80,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}各个角度收集光线\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from any spot in its field of view
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.84,0:12:29.81,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}遍布整个镜片或者镜子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}across the entire lens or mirror,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.84,0:12:33.54,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}开孔要比照相机暗箱的小孔大许多\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}an opening much larger than the camera obscura hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.58,0:12:37.48,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这是最早的望远镜之一\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is one of the first telescopes...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.51,0:12:41.58,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}伽利略在1609年使用过的那个\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the one that Galileo looked through in 1609.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.62,0:12:45.86,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他用这个掀开了黑夜的厚重幕布\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}With it, he pulled aside the heavy curtain of night
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.89,0:12:48.79,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}并且开始发现宇宙\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and began to discover the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.40,0:13:03.41,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}都归功于镜片\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The lens made it possible
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.44,0:13:06.51,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}镜片为望远镜提供了比我们眼睛\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for a telescope to have a much larger light-collecting area
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.54,0:13:08.84,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}更大的光线收集区域\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}than our eyes have.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.88,0:13:12.28,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}大桶比小桶可以收集更多的雨水\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Big buckets catch more rain than small ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.32,0:13:15.22,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}现代的望远镜拥有更大收集区域\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Modern telescopes have larger collecting areas,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.25,0:13:16.92,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}高度敏感的探测器\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}highly sensitive detectors,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.95,0:13:19.86,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}并可以长时间锁定同一目标\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and they track the same object for hours at a time
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.89,0:13:23.23,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}以搜集尽可能多的光线\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to accumulate as much of its light as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.26,0:13:26.03,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}像哈勃 这样的太空望远镜\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Space-based telescopes such as the Hubble,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.06,0:13:27.90,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}搜集来自最久远星系的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}have captured light from the most distant
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.93,0:13:29.57,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}光线\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and ancient galaxies,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.60,0:13:32.77,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}为我们带来大量的更清晰的宇宙图片\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}giving us vastly clearer pictures of the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.40,0:13:38.11,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}海桑发现了光线成像的原理\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Al-Hazen discovered how images are formed by light,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.14,0:13:40.48,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但这并不是他最最伟大的成就\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but that was far from his greatest achievement.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.51,0:13:43.21,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他是有史以来设定\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Ibn al-Hazen was the first person ever
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.25,0:13:45.92,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}科学原则的第一人\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to set down the rules of science.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.95,0:13:48.45,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他创造了一套纠错机制\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He created an error-correcting mechanism,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.49,0:13:50.95,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一套系统的 严格的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a systematic and relentless way
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.99,0:13:53.62,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}审查错误观念的机制\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to sift out misconceptions in our thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.66,0:13:58.63,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}探究真相是困难的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Finding truth is difficult...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.66,0:14:01.63,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}探究真相的道路是崎岖的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the road to it is rough.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.67,0:14:03.93,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}作为追寻真相的人\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As seekers after truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.97,0:14:07.07,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}不轻易下判断 不轻信古人所云\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you will be wise to withhold judgment and not simply put
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.10,0:14:09.97,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}是十分明智的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}your trust in the writings of the ancients.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.01,0:14:13.81,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你必须质疑并且谨慎的验证这些理论\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You must question and critically examine those writings
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.84,0:14:16.35,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}从各个角度\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from every side.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.38,0:14:19.62,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你只能接受论据和实验的结果\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You must submit only to argument and experiment
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.65,0:14:23.02,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}而不是别人的说法\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and not to the sayings of any person.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.05,0:14:25.59,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}因为每个人都有弱点\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For every human being is vulnerable
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.62,0:14:28.29,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}没有人是完美的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to all kinds of imperfection.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.33,0:14:30.76,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}作为寻求真相的人\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As seekers after truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.79,0:14:33.13,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们必须怀疑并质疑\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we must also suspect and question
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.16,0:14:36.77,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们自己的理论  反复论证\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}our own ideas as we perform our investigations,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.80,0:14:41.70,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}避免陷入偏见与疏忽\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to avoid falling into prejudice or careless thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.74,0:14:46.98,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}接受这些方针  真相就在眼前\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Take this course, and truth will be revealed to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.86,0:15:07.03,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这就是科学的方式\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is the method of science.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.06,0:15:09.87,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}得益于此 我们的机器人大使可以\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So powerful that it's carried our robotic emissaries
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.90,0:15:13.34,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}航行到太阳系的边缘乃至无限的宇宙\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to the edge of the solar system and beyond.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.07,0:15:17.37,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它扩展了我们的生命长度\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It has doubled our lifespan,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.41,0:15:19.17,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}将过去的失落世界\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}made the lost worlds of the past
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.21,0:15:21.21,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}带回现在\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}come alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.61,0:15:24.85,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}科学使我们可以对遥远的未来\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Science has enabled us to predict events
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.88,0:15:27.35,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}做出预测\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the distant future...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.38,0:15:30.85,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}让我们可以彼此以光速交流\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and to communicate with each other at the speed of light,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.89,0:15:33.49,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就像你我之间  此时此刻\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as I am with you, right at this moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.52,0:15:35.56,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这种思考的方式带给我们力量\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This way of thinking has given us powers
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.59,0:15:39.23,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那种海桑都认为神奇的力量\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that al-Hazen himself would have regarded as wizardry.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.73,0:15:47.10,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他将我们带上这条崎岖 无尽的道路\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But it was he who put us on this rough, endless road.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.97,0:15:51.84,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}将我们带到一个地方\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And now it has taken us to a place
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.88,0:15:56.58,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在那里即使光线也被黑暗掩盖\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}where even light itself is enshrouded in darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.50,0:16:08.63,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}光线有着独一无二的属性\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Light has properties unlike anything else
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.67,0:16:10.54,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}以人类存在的领域来说\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the realm of human existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.57,0:16:12.71,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}比如光的速度\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Take the speed of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.74,0:16:14.84,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}光的基础微粒  光子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The basic particle of light, the photon,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.87,0:16:17.54,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当它从原子或分子中诞生时\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is born traveling at the speed of light
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.58,0:16:20.35,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就有光的速度\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as it emerges from an atom or a molecule.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.38,0:16:22.51,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}也只有这一种速度\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A photon never knows any other speed,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.55,0:16:25.35,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们尚未发现其它任何可以立即\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and we've not found another phenomenon that accelerates
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.39,0:16:28.32,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}从0加速到速度极限的现象\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from zero to top speed instantaneously.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.36,0:16:30.56,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}没有别的东西可以移动这么快\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Nothing else could move as fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.59,0:16:33.23,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当我们尝试将其它粒子不断加速\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When we try to accelerate other particles closer and closer
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.26,0:16:35.96,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}越接近光速  阻力越大\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to the speed of light, they resist more and more,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.00,0:16:37.73,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}并且越来越重\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as though they're getting heavier and heavier.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.76,0:16:39.20,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}还没有任何实验可以\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}No experiment yet devised
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.23,0:16:43.24,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}将粒子将速度到光的速度\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}has ever made a particle move as fast as light.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.91,0:16:52.54,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}哪是什么\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.58,0:16:54.75,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你听了吗\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You hear something?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.78,0:16:56.92,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}说到哪了 哦 对了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Where was I? Oh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.95,0:17:01.02,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}没有什么可以像光那样\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I don't know anything else in life that behaves like light.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.05,0:17:04.49,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我无法将它这种与众不同的属性\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I cannot reconcile its strange properties
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.52,0:17:07.16,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}与我其它的感官相调谐\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with everything else my senses tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.19,0:17:07.19,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们相信我们的感官胜过\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our urge to trust our senses overpowers
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.20,0:17:12.26,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}测量仪器对于\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}what our measuring devices tell us about
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.30,0:17:14.20,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}实际情况的结果\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the actual nature of reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.23,0:17:16.40,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们的感官对于普通尺寸物体的普通速度来说\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our senses work fine for life-size objects
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.44,0:17:18.24,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}没有问题\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}moving at mammal speeds,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.27,0:17:22.88,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但是却不适用于光速那些神奇的规则\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but are ill-adapted for the wonderland laws of lightspeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.05,0:17:30.42,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们甚至不明白为什么会有宇宙速度极限\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We don't even know why there's a cosmic speed limit.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.45,0:17:33.89,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}时间在达到光速时静止\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Time stands still when you're traveling at the speed of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.92,0:17:36.39,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}到底什么是光\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What is light, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.93,0:17:43.43,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}艾萨克・牛顿始终对光非常着迷\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Isaac Newton's enduring fascination with light
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.46,0:17:45.63,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}从他还是个孩子时\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}began when he was a child...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.07,0:17:50.50,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就在这个房子里\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in this very house.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.58,0:17:59.75,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他在弱冠之年  就是第一位\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}By the time he was in his 20s, Newton became the first person
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.78,0:18:02.95,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}破译彩虹奥秘的人\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to decipher the mystery of the rainbow.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.65,0:18:09.96,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}牛顿发现有些光  白光\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Newton discovered that some light, or white light,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.99,0:18:12.96,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}由所有彩虹的颜色混合而成\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is a mixture of all the colors of the rainbow.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.50,0:18:17.56,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}重大的发现\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Major discovery.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.60,0:18:20.13,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他将之称为 光谱\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He named the displays of colors a "spectrum"
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.17,0:18:24.44,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}来源于拉丁语中的幻影 或者幽灵\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from the Latin for "phantom" or "apparition."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.68,0:18:38.65,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}牛大师 抱歉打扰了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Begging your pardon, Master Newton,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.69,0:18:41.39,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}晚饭再不吃就要坏了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the cook frets that your dinner will spoil, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.29,0:18:46.46,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}呀麦蝶 小牛 别把放大镜放下\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}No, Isaac, don't put the magnifying glass down!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.49,0:18:50.26,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}光里还有更神奇的东西\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Something even more amazing is hidden in the light--
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.30,0:18:52.80,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一串密码  一条通向宇宙的钥匙\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a code, a key to the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.57,0:19:03.48,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}牛顿错过了很重要的一项发现\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Isaac Newton didn't miss much, but that one was a beaut.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.51,0:19:06.61,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他错过了那扇通向神秘宇宙的门\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He just walked right past the door to a hidden universe;
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.65,0:19:10.68,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那扇门直到150年后才再次开启\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a door that would not swing open again for another 150 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.72,0:19:13.02,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}归功于另一位科学家\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It would fall on another scientist,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.05,0:19:14.72,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}1800年 在工作时\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}working in the year 1800,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.75,0:19:16.72,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}无意间发现了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to stumble on a piece of evidence
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.26,0:19:20.26,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们周围无可见世界的证据\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for the unseen worlds that surround us.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.83,0:19:26.26,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}晚上  威廉・赫歇尔搜索天空\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}By night, William Herschel scanned the heavens
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.30,0:19:28.77,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}使用当时最大的望远镜\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with the largest telescope of his time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.80,0:19:31.74,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}白天  赫歇尔做实验\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}By day, Herschel performed experiments.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.77,0:19:34.41,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}根据牛顿的研究结果  已知日光\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}From Newton's earlier work, it was known that sunlight
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.44,0:19:36.81,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}由不同颜色的光混合而成\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is a blend of different colors.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.84,0:19:39.21,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}所有人都知道  在户外\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And everyone knew, just from being outside,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.24,0:19:41.44,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}日光带来热量\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that sunlight carries heat.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.98,0:19:44.98,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}威廉赫歇尔不禁疑问\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}William Herschel asked
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.02,0:19:47.58,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}哪种颜色的光带着更多的热量\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}whether some colors of light carry more heat than others.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.62,0:19:51.72,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}科学天才的天性就是对那些\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The nature of scientific genius is to question
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.76,0:19:54.56,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们认为理所当然的事情产生疑问\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}what the rest of us take for granted...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.59,0:19:57.16,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}然后做用实验证实\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and then do the experiment.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.20,0:20:02.63,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}赫歇尔放在光照范围之外的温度计\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The thermometer that Herschel placed outside the spectrum
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.67,0:20:04.67,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}是他的对照物\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}was his control.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.37,0:20:08.27,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}对照物在实验中\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The control in any experiment
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.30,0:20:10.94,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}不参加实验操作\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}always lacks the factor being tested.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.97,0:20:13.07,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这样才能知道你的实验物\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That way, you know if what you're testing is
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.11,0:20:15.21,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}是否真的是对实验本身产生反应\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}really the thing responsible for the observation.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.34,0:20:17.65,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在赫歇尔的试验中\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In Herschel's experiment,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.68,0:20:19.28,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}验证的是\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the relationship between
