Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.72,0:20:23.79,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他用一个温度计做对照\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and so his control was a thermometer
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.82,0:20:25.49,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}放在白纸上\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}over the part of the white sheet
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.52,0:20:28.82,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}日光照射之外\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that was not illuminated by sunlight at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.16,0:20:32.69,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那个声音又来了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There's that sound again.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.73,0:20:35.46,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}到底是什么\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.20,0:20:43.70,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}红光比蓝光产生更多的热\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Okay, red light is warmer than blue light.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.74,0:20:48.81,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}有趣的发现 但还不算惊天动地\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Interesting discovery, but not exactly revolutionary.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.33,0:21:14.03,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你的温度计没有问题\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}No, there's nothing wrong with your thermometer.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.07,0:21:17.43,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你只是发现了一种新的光\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You've just discovered a new kind of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.28,0:21:29.35,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}赫歇尔是首位发现在光谱中\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Herschel was the first to detect this unseen presence
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.38,0:21:32.58,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}红色以外或以下 不可见光的人\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lurking just below the red end of the spectrum.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.62,0:21:35.52,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这就是红外线名字的由来\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's why it came to be called "infrared."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.62,0:21:35.52,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}红外线=infra red
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.55,0:21:37.72,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}英语的infra在拉丁语中意为 之下\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}"Infra" is Latin for the word "below."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.75,0:21:39.32,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它不可见\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's invisible.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.36,0:21:41.72,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们的眼睛对这类光不敏感\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our eyes are not sensitive to this kind of light,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.76,0:21:44.63,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们的皮肤不同  我们可以感受到热\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but our skin is-- we feel it as heat.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.66,0:21:46.46,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这才是真正的重大发现\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now, that's a really big discovery.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.50,0:21:48.90,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但是光线之中依然隐藏着\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But far greater secrets were still hiding
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.93,0:21:51.40,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}更大的秘密\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}deep inside the light.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.15,0:22:01.18,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}几乎与威廉赫歇尔在英格兰\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}At about the same time that William Herschel
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.22,0:22:04.12,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}发现红外线的同时\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}was discovering infrared light in his parlor in England,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.15,0:22:06.62,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一位名叫约瑟夫・夫琅和费的孩子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a young boy named Joseph Fraunhofer
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.66,0:22:09.12,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}从事着乏味的繁重的工作\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}was trapped in hopeless drudgery.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.16,0:22:12.09,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他站在盛满有毒化学物的熔炉旁\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He stood over a cauldron of toxic chemicals
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.13,0:22:14.50,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}不断地搅拌\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and endlessly stirred.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.40,0:22:19.20,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}约瑟夫11岁时成了孤儿\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Joseph had been orphaned at the age of 11
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.23,0:22:23.04,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}被送给苛刻的维塞伯格\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and given to a harsh master named Weichselberger,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.07,0:22:26.01,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他替皇家做镜子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the royal mirror-maker.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.04,0:22:28.31,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他不让约瑟夫去上学\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He prevented Joseph from going to school.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.34,0:22:33.51,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}而是白天让约瑟夫在玻璃作坊做苦力\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Instead, Joseph labored in the glass-making workshop by day,
