Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.50,0:34:51.37,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}将电子束缚在轨道上的力量\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The force that holds an electron in orbit
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.40,0:34:53.20,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}和重力没有丝毫关系\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}has nothing to do with gravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.24,0:34:56.77,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它是电气引力\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's a force of electrical attraction.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.81,0:34:59.11,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}电子沿着波浪形的圆环\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The electron dances a wavy ring
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.14,0:35:01.64,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}环绕氢原子的原子核运行\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}around the central nucleus of a hydrogen atom.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.81,0:35:04.58,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}从一个轨道跳到另一个轨道\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And makes quantum leaps from orbit to orbit.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.85,0:35:05.12,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}忽上忽下\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Up or down.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.16,0:35:06.52,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}轨道越大\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The larger the orbit,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.56,0:35:08.59,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}电子的能量越大\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the greater the energy of an electron.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.63,0:35:12.99,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}电子必须获取能量才能跳跃到更大的轨道上\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}An electron has to get energy to leap to a larger orbit.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.20,0:35:16.00,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}然后必须释放能量才能跳回来\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And it has to lose energy to jump back down.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.03,0:35:22.33,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}每次向上的跳跃都是原子吸收光波的结果\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Every upward leap is caused by... an atom absorbing a light wave.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.81,0:35:26.61,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们还不知道是什么使它向下跳跃\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But we have no idea what causes the downward leaps.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.64,0:35:30.21,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们只知道向下跳跃产生光波\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What we do know that such leaps always produce a light wave
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.25,0:35:34.88,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这种光波的颜色与轨道间的能量差异相吻合\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}whose color matches the energy difference between the orbitals.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.59,0:35:43.99,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}太阳的表面辐射出所有颜色的光波\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Sun's surface radiates light waves of all colors.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.03,0:35:45.83,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如果你透过棱镜看日光\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If you look at sunlight through a prism,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.86,0:35:47.86,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你能看到它的光谱\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you'll see its spectrum.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.50,0:35:53.34,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当你用望远镜放大光谱时\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When you magnify the spectrum with a telescope,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.37,0:35:55.24,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就像约瑟夫・夫琅和费那样\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as Joseph Fraunhofer did,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.27,0:35:56.84,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你就可以窥视\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you raise the curtain
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.87,0:36:00.08,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}电子在原子中跳跃的真相\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}on the electron dance within the atom.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.11,0:36:02.31,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当电子的能量衰弱\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When the energy of the electron flags,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.35,0:36:04.01,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它降到较低的轨道时\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and it drops to a lower orbital,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.05,0:36:06.42,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}光波逸散\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the light wave it emits scatters.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.45,0:36:08.85,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}大多数不会到我们这里\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Most of it doesn't reach us.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.89,0:36:10.42,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这就留下了一个黑暗的空当\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That leaves a dark gap
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.45,0:36:13.36,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}或者说 光谱中的黑色竖线\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or black vertical line in the spectrum.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.39,0:36:15.92,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这些黑线就是\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These dark lines are the shadows
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.96,0:36:19.56,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}氢原子在太阳大气层中造成的阴影\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}cast by hydrogen atoms in the atmosphere of the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.56,0:36:22.26,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}钠原子发出不同的阴影\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Sodium atoms cast different shadows.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.30,0:36:25.37,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他们的电子按照不同的曲子跳舞\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Their electrons dance to a different tune.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.40,0:36:29.08,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一粒盐由钠原子和氯原子组成\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A grain of table salt is composed of sodium and chlorine atoms.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.14,0:36:33.57,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}千万亿的原子疯狂地舞动\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Ten million billion of them doing their crazy dances
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.61,0:36:36.45,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}仅仅是在一粒盐中\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in a single grain of salt.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.48,0:36:39.38,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一个铁原子有26个电子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And a single iron atom with 26 electrons
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.42,0:36:44.75,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}庞大的宛如百老汇音乐剧的制作团队\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is like a great big production number in a Broadway musical.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.49,0:36:51.39,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当你用分光仪观察星星时\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When you look at a star with a spectroscope,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.43,0:36:55.53,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在它大气层中所有元素上都能看到黑线\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you see the dark lines from all the elements in its atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.57,0:36:57.43,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}给我任意一个物体的光谱\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Show me the spectrum of anything,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.47,0:37:00.24,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}不论是在地球上的 还是在遥远的星星上\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}whether here on Earth or from a distant star,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.27,0:37:03.31,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我都可以告诉你 它的元素构成\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and I'll tell you what it's made of.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.34,0:37:06.94,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}夫琅和费线是元素的原子签名\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Fraunhofer's lines are the atomic signatures
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.98,0:37:10.95,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}遍布整个宇宙\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of the elements writ large across the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.98,0:37:13.05,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如同科学历史上的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As with every other major revelation
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.08,0:37:15.58,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}其它重大发现一样  它带来了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the history of science, it opened the way
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.62,0:37:18.59,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}更新更深层次的谜团\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to newer and deeper mysteries.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.62,0:37:21.59,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}还有更多地\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And to the revelation that there were
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.62,0:37:24.66,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}秘密依然藏在光线中\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}many more secrets hiding in the light.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.59,0:37:43.52,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当夫琅和费把望远镜和棱镜结合在一起\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When Joseph Fraunhofer combined a prism with a telescope
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.53,0:37:45.79,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}用它们探索天空\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and turned it toward the skies,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.80,0:37:49.30,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他将星星与我们之间的距离缩短了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}he brought the stars much closer to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.28,0:38:03.01,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他39岁时\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When he was only 39,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.01,0:38:05.18,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他身患重病\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}he contracted a fatal illness.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.18,0:38:07.85,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}可能是由于早年长期曝露在\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Perhaps as a result of his early and long-term exposure
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.85,0:38:10.78,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}制作玻璃的有毒化学物质的缘故\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to the toxic chemicals of glassmaking.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.79,0:38:14.79,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你永远不知道下一个天才在何处诞生\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You never know where the next genius will come from.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.73,0:38:23.23,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}不知道我们错过了多少天才\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}How many of them do we leave in the rubble?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.23,0:38:26.50,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}对一位孤儿的善行给王子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The prince and his kingdom were immeasurably enriched
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.50,0:38:29.87,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}和他的王国带来不可计量的财富\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}by that act of kindness to a poor orphan.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.87,0:38:32.31,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}夫琅和费的发现将巴伐利亚\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Fraunhofer's discoveries transformed Bavaria
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.31,0:38:36.58,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}从偏僻的乡下变成高科技的制造中心\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from a rural backwater to a technological powerhouse.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.41,0:38:40.85,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在他弥留之际  政府急切地\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As he lay dying, the government was desperate
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.85,0:38:43.75,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}想要保留他所有的关于\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to preserve every shred of his precious knowledge
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.75,0:38:46.05,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}高科技光学玻璃的宝贵知识\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}about the high technology of optical glass.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.09,0:38:51.03,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但这只能让一个人知道\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But it could only be divulged to a person
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.03,0:38:53.23,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}此人有着最高级别的涉密权限\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with top security clearance--
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.23,0:38:55.00,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}铸币局主管\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the director of the mint.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.08,0:39:14.68,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}政府保留了夫琅和费的技术\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The government kept Fraunhofer's technology
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.68,0:39:16.58,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}用于制造完美的光学玻璃\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for making perfect optical glass
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.59,0:39:19.85,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一个上百年的国家机密\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a State secret for another hundred years.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.86,0:39:22.86,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}后来证明这给某人带来很大的阻碍\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This would prove to be a major obstacle
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.89,0:39:24.36,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}以后我们会提到\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for someone we'll meet later in our journey.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.39,0:39:26.93,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但夫琅和费不能容忍这样\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But Fraunhofer would allow no such secrecy
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.96,0:39:29.53,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}对他的科学研究保密\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}where his pure scientific research was concerned.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.56,0:39:33.17,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他知道科学需要开放才能昌盛\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He knew that science requires openness to flourish;
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.20,0:39:37.24,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们对于自然地了解属于全世界\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that our understanding of nature belongs to the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.27,0:39:40.17,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}夫琅和费发现谱线后\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As soon as Fraunhofer discovered the spectral lines,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.21,0:39:42.74,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他立即发表了所有的成果\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}he published everything he knew about them.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.78,0:39:45.58,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如此重要的发现带来的影响\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And the reverberations of his momentous discovery
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.61,0:39:48.38,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}持续至今\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}echo still.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.55,0:39:55.52,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他的谱线揭示了可观测宇宙\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}His spectral lines revealed that the visible cosmos
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.56,0:39:58.83,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}是由相同的元素构成\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is all made of the same elements.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.86,0:40:04.33,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}行星们\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The planets...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.47,0:40:14.94,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}恒星们\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The stars...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.31,0:40:21.45,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}星系们\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The galaxies...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.69,0:40:28.69,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们  还有所有的生命体\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We, ourselves, and all of life...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.36,0:40:38.90,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}拥有共同的物质\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The same star stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.34,0:40:46.01,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他让我们知道了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He made it possible for us to know
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.04,0:40:48.51,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}其它星球的大气层中有些什么\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}what's in the atmosphere of other worlds.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.98,0:40:54.62,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}远在上百万光年外的星系中\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And in galaxies millions of light-years away.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.65,0:40:57.65,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}谱线不止揭示了遥远物体的成分\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Spectral lines revealed not only the composition
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.68,0:41:01.36,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}也揭示了他们是在靠近还是远离我们\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of far-off objects, but also their motion towards or away from us.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.39,0:41:04.46,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}通过它 我们发现我们的宇宙还在扩张\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Using them, we discovered that our universe is expanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.49,0:41:08.06,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但分光仪最伟大的作用\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But perhaps the greatest revelation of spectroscopy
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.10,0:41:10.90,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}是发现了不可见光\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is the discovery of the thing it cannot see.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.91,0:41:19.07,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}暗物质的隐蔽宇宙\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A hidden universe of dark matter
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.11,0:41:22.34,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}质量比我们熟悉的宇宙超出6倍\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}six times more massive than the familiar cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.38,0:41:24.54,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}由某些神秘的物质组成\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's made of some mysterious substance
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.58,0:41:29.15,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}不会发出 反射或者吸收任何形式的光\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that does not emit, reflect or absorb any kind of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.18,0:41:31.65,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}因为它的引力我们才知道它的存在\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We only know it's there because of its gravity,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.69,0:41:33.75,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它的引力吸引着星系\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which pulls on all the galaxies
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.79,0:41:36.52,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}并为其中的恒星加速\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and speeds up the visible stars within them.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.53,0:41:44.00,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们的眼睛可以看见很多种类的光\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There are many more kinds of light than our eyes can see.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.03,0:41:47.43,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}认为我们的自然只有可见光\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Confining our perception of nature to visible light
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.47,0:41:49.77,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就如同听的音乐\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is like listening to music
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.80,0:41:51.37,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}只有一个八度\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in only one octave.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.94,0:41:55.94,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}其实还有很多很多\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There are so many more.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.98,0:41:57.91,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他们仅仅是波长的区别\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They differ only in wavelength,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.95,0:42:00.05,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}只是范围很大\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but over a huge range.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.08,0:42:02.65,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}比如 红外线\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For instance, infrared light...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.99,0:42:11.12,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}威廉费歇尔发现的那种\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the kind that William Herschel discovered
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.16,0:42:12.93,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}X光\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Or X-ray light.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.00,0:42:20.07,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}无线电波\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Or radio light.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.81,0:42:26.64,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}伽马射线\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Or in gamma-ray light.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.45,0:42:35.72,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}不仅是看东西的方式不同\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These are not just different ways of seeing the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.75,0:42:37.32,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}不同的光\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These other kinds of light
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.35,0:42:40.95,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}揭示出宇宙中不同的物体和现象\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}reveal different objects and phenomena in the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.99,0:42:43.16,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}比方说通过伽马射线 它使我们可以\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In gamma-ray light, for example, we can see mysterious explosions
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.19,0:42:45.93,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}不再错过\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in distant galaxies
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.96,0:42:48.26,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}遥远星系的神秘爆炸\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that we would otherwise miss.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.20,0:42:54.07,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}通过微波 我们可以看到\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And in microwave light, we can see all the way back
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.10,0:42:56.50,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}宇宙诞生之初的情景\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to the birth of the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.04,0:43:02.34,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们只不过才刚刚开始睁开眼睛\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We have only just opened our eyes.
